description:
Hi, my name is Anuk and I'm a Barbet (french waterdog). I loooooove dogs! That's why I'm always looking for friends to play with. If you read this and know some friendly paws, who might want to join me running around in nature – sign up for this group and hopefully see you soon!

____

PS: this group is self-organized, everybody becomes an assistant organizer and is welcome to announce events! Looking forward to a lot of nice walks. See you soon, Ela & Anuk.

description: Attention all puppies in Zürich... come play! This group is for those of us who own a puppy under 1 year, and who would like for their pup to socialise with other furry friends. category.name: pets/animals
description: For the French Bulldog owners of Zurich! Meeting the last Sunday of each month at Rieter Park at 1pm. Will meet at Museum entrance off of Seestrasse. If you are one of the first arrivals, look for out for the bat ears and walk towards them. We will leave 15 minutes for late arrivals before starting our slow walk around the park. Intermittent stop offs will likely occur! Will finish at the museum cafe where you can stay and chat, leave, or do absolutely whatever you like! The frenchies will have the final decision, I'm sure. This group is for French Bulldogs but English Bulldogs, Boston Terriers, and Pugs are welcome accomplices. I hope to see you all there for the first frenchie meet up! Here is the link to Mueseum Rietberg and remember we will meet by the entrance on seestrasse: http://www.rietberg.ch/de-ch/foyer.aspx
name: Zürich French Bulldog Meetup Group

description:

____

PS: this group is self-organized, everybody becomes an assistant organizer and is welcome to announce events! Looking forward to a lot of nice walks. See you soon, Ela & Anuk.

Wir treffen uns jeden Freitag 19 Uhr auf dem Ponyhof Bätterkinden um als Zuschauer dem Mounted Games Training beizuwohnen. Kleiner Apéro kann mitgebracht werden.

category.name: pets/animals
description: For the French Bulldog owners of Zurich! Meeting the last Sunday of each month at Rieter Park at 1pm. Will meet at Museum entrance off of Seestrasse. If you are one of the first arrivals, look for out for the bat ears and walk towards them. We will leave 15 minutes for late arrivals before starting our slow walk around the park. Intermittent stop offs will likely occur! Will finish at the museum cafe where you can stay and chat, leave, or do absolutely whatever you like! The frenchies will have the final decision, I'm sure. This group is for French Bulldogs but English Bulldogs, Boston Terriers, and Pugs are welcome accomplices. I hope to see you all there for the first frenchie meet up! Here is the link to Mueseum Rietberg and remember we will meet by the entrance on seestrasse: http://www.rietberg.ch/de-ch/foyer.aspx
name: Zürich French Bulldog Meetup Group

description:
Hi, my name is Anuk and I'm a Barbet (french waterdog). I loooooove dogs! That's why I'm always looking for friends to play with. If you read this and know some friendly paws, who might want to join me running around in nature – sign up for this group and hopefully see you soon!

____

PS: this group is self-organized, everybody becomes an assistant organizer and is welcome to announce events! Looking forward to a lot of nice walks. See you soon, Ela & Anuk.

category.name: pets/animals
description:
Who Should Join?
People with big hearts who genuinely love pets (cats more exactly), coffee, thrillers, jazz, and cozy evenings with friends and family

What our Meetup Group is About?  Getting together people who love cats, books, coffee, making friends, have a great time together sharing the same interests and exchange advice about healthy food prepared with care for our pets and how to find REALLY NATURAL food at convenient prices. An important detail: the food I want to talk to you about cannot be found at the vet's or supermarkets

Why You Should Join? To have a relaxing after work time, petting a cat while reading, sipping coffee, listening to good music, talking with friends

What Members Can Expect?  The specific of Geneva area is that people are moving in and out regularly, they are commuting every day, have long days of work and do not have the opportunity and time to make friends. There are lots of fun places in here, still there is none like ours and this is why our Members will meet with people who love the same things, share the same passions, have a delicious cup of coffee freshly roasted just round the corner, and enjoy cats' soothing presence. Our place is designed for those who love cats but cannot adopt any for various reasons such as a landlord who doesn't allow them to have a pet, long hours of work, recurrent travelling periods of time, regular change of countries for professional reasons, and many other reasons one can imagine. 

You can also have a look at our group page
name: Cats' P.l.ayce Bookshop-Café with Adopted Cats to Open Soon

category.name: pets/animals
description:
If you live in the Geneva area (Switzerland) and have (or don't have but love) dogs and also love hiking, this is the group for you !

This group is also for you if you are considering getting a dog but not sure what life with a dog in Geneva would entail - join us and we'll be happy to share our experiences.

Let's get together and discover the region with our four-legged companions.

Also find this group on www.glocals.com and on Facebook; "Geneva Hiking with Dogs".

You're welcome to post questions to the rest of the group about hiking with dogs, or just about dogs in general in Geneva!

category.name: pets/animals
description: For the French Bulldog owners of Zurich! Meeting the last Sunday of each month at Rieter Park at 1pm. Will meet at Museum entrance off of Seestrasse. If you are one of the first arrivals, look for out for the bat ears and walk towards them. We will leave 15 minutes for late arrivals before starting our slow walk around the park. Intermittent stop offs will likely occur! Will finish at the museum cafe where you can stay and chat, leave, or do absolutely whatever you like! The frenchies will have the final decision, I'm sure. This group is for French Bulldogs but English Bulldogs, Boston Terriers, and Pugs are welcome accomplices. I hope to see you all there for the first frenchie meet up! Here is the link to Mueseum Rietberg and remember we will meet by the entrance on seestrasse: http://www.rietberg.ch/de-ch/foyer.aspx
name: Zürich French Bulldog Meetup Group

category.name: pets/animals
description:
Hi, my name is Anuk and I'm a Barbet (french waterdog). I loooooove dogs! That's why I'm always looking for friends to play with. If you read this and know some friendly paws, who might want to join me running around in nature – sign up for this group and hopefully see you soon!

____

PS: this group is self-organized, everybody becomes an assistant organizer and is welcome to announce events! Looking forward to a lot of nice walks. See you soon, Ela & Anuk.

description: Attention all puppies in Zürich... come play! This group is for those of us who own a puppy under 1 year, and who would like for their pup to socialise with other furry friends. We will meet at a different park or grassy area every weekend to help our puppies socialise. Once a month my partner Jan and I will organise a short hike and picnic nearby the city. Bonito, our sweet three month old Border Collie / Maremmano mix looks forward to having some fun with you at our next Meetup!

category.name: pets/animals
description: For the French Bulldog owners of Zurich! Meeting the last Sunday of each month at Rieter Park at 1pm. Will meet at Museum entrance off of Seestrasse. If you are one of the first arrivals, look for out for the bat ears and walk towards them. We will leave 15 minutes for late arrivals before starting our slow walk around the park. Intermittent stop offs will likely occur! Will finish at the museum cafe where you can stay and chat, leave, or do absolutely whatever you like! The frenchies will have the final decision, I'm sure. This group is for French Bulldogs but English Bulldogs, Boston Terriers, and Pugs are welcome accomplices. I hope to see you all there for the first frenchie meet up! Here is the link to Mueseum Rietberg and remember we will meet by the entrance on seestrasse: http://www.rietberg.ch/de-ch/foyer.aspx
name: Zürich French Bulldog Meetup Group

category.name: pets/animals
description:
Hi, my name is Anuk and I'm a Barbet (french waterdog). I loooooove dogs! That's why I'm always looking for friends to play with. If you read this and know some friendly paws, who might want to join me running around in nature – sign up for this group and hopefully see you soon!

____

PS: this group is self-organized, everybody becomes an assistant organizer and is welcome to announce events! Looking forward to a lot of nice walks. See you soon, Ela & Anuk.

description:
Wir treffen uns jeden Freitag 19 Uhr auf dem Ponyhof Bätterkinden um als Zuschauer dem Mounted Games Training beizuwohnen. Kleiner Apéro kann mitgebracht werden.
Ziel:
Gemütlichkeit und Gedankenaustausch zu den Themen: Reiten lernen, Ausreiten ins Gelände, wettkampfmässiger Pferdesport im allgemeinen und Pony Mounted Games im speziellen. Kennen lernen von Pferde- und Pony-begeisterten Leuten aus der Region und aus fernen Ländern.
name: Ponyhof Bätterkinden/Stall Schneider Meinisberg Meetup Bern

category.name: pets/animals
description:
Who Should Join?
People with big hearts who genuinely love pets (cats more exactly), coffee, thrillers, jazz, and cozy evenings with friends and family

What our Meetup Group is About?  Getting together people who love cats, books, coffee, making friends, have a great time together sharing the same interests and exchange advice about healthy food prepared with care for our pets and how to find REALLY NATURAL food at convenient prices. An important detail: the food I want to talk to you about cannot be found at the vet's or supermarkets

Why You Should Join? To have a relaxing after work time, petting a cat while reading, sipping coffee, listening to good music, talking with friends

What Members Can Expect?  The specific of Geneva area is that people are moving in and out regularly, they are commuting every day, have long days of work and do not have the opportunity and time to make friends. There are lots of fun places in here, still there is none like ours and this is why our Members will meet with people who love the same things, share the same passions, have a delicious cup of coffee freshly roasted just round the corner, and enjoy cats' soothing presence. Our place is designed for those who love cats but cannot adopt any for various reasons such as a landlord who doesn't allow them to have a pet, long hours of work, recurrent travelling periods of time, regular change of countries for professional reasons, and many other reasons one can imagine. 

You can also have a look at our group page
name: Cats' P.l.ayce Bookshop-Café with Adopted Cats to Open Soon

category.name: pets/animals
description:
If you live in the Geneva area (Switzerland) and have (or don't have but love) dogs and also love hiking, this is the group for you !

This group is also for you if you are considering getting a dog but not sure what life with a dog in Geneva would entail - join us and we'll be happy to share our experiences.

Let's get together and discover the region with our four-legged companions.

Also find this group on www.glocals.com and on Facebook; "Geneva Hiking with Dogs".

You're welcome to post questions to the rest of the group about hiking with dogs, or just about dogs in general in Geneva!
name: Geneva Hiking with Dogs

What Members Can Expect?  The specific of Geneva area is that people are moving in and out regularly, they are commuting every day, have long days of work and do not have the opportunity and time to make friends. There are lots of fun places in here, still there is none like ours and this is why our Members will meet with people who love the same things, share the same passions, have a delicious cup of coffee freshly roasted just round the corner, and enjoy cats' soothing presence. Our place is designed for those who love cats but cannot adopt any for various reasons such as a landlord who doesn't allow them to have a pet, long hours of work, recurrent travelling periods of time, regular change of countries for professional reasons, and many other reasons one can imagine. 

You can also have a look at our group page

description:
If you live in the Geneva area (Switzerland) and have (or don't have but love) dogs and also love hiking, this is the group for you !

This group is also for you if you are considering getting a dog but not sure what life with a dog in Geneva would entail - join us and we'll be happy to share our experiences.

Let's get together and discover the region with our four-legged companions.

Also find this group on www.glocals.com and on Facebook; "Geneva Hiking with Dogs".

You're welcome to post questions to the rest of the group about hiking with dogs, or just about dogs in general in Geneva!
